US authorities forced Mask to leave the post of chairman of Tesla
American businessman Ilon Musk will leave the post of chairman of the Tesla company he founded at the request of the US government.
To settle the claims of the Federal Securities and Exchange Commission, the entrepreneur will also pay $ 20 million.
According to CNBC, the pre-trial agreement with the agency allows the Mask to remain in the leading position at Tesla.
At the same time, he is obliged to pay $ 20 million and leave the post of chairman of the board of directors within 45 days from the time of the agreement and for at least three years.
