Every inhabitant of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the republic are increasingly visiting the official website of the Office of the Federal Bailiff Service of Russia in Kazakhstan.
According to the specialists of the department of organizational and control work, informatization and information security of the republican department, over the past eight months more than 140 thousand visits to the site were registered, more than 42 thousand were registered in the "Data Bank of Enforcement Proceedings" section, 661 debts were paid.
According to Valery Bogdanov, chairman of the Public Council at the UFSSP of Russia in Kazakhstan, practically every citizen of the region has debts for utility bills, traffic police fines, bank loans, loans, and no one is immune from unforeseen situations.
But debtors can expect negative consequences in the form of, for example, a ban on leaving abroad.
That is why the Federal Bailiff Service of Russia in Kazakhstan recommends that anyone who has planned a trip abroad, check with the bailiffs department at their place of residence or on the website www.r08fssprus.ru for information about the presence of unpaid debts and pay them off.
The service has created a “Databank of enforcement proceedings” for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is available not only on the regional sites of the UFSSP of Russia, but also on social networks and mobile phones of the iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The data bank contains information on enforcement proceedings initiated by Kalmyk police officers against all debtors, ”explains Delgir Bodgayeva, assistant to the head of the UFSSP of Russia in Kazakhstan.
“If there are debts, the system displays information on the number and date of the commencement of the enforcement proceedings; the name of the authority that issued the enforcement order or other act; its number, amount and type of debt;
Information on the course of enforcement proceedings can also be obtained on the public services portal at: http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru "
